      <div class="docs-eyebrow">Admin Panel</div>
      <h1 class="docs-title">Widget Panels</h1>
      <p class="docs-lead">
        Widget Panels are editable content areas rendered in fixed positions on the board —
        the site header and footer. Each panel holds free-form rich text and BBCode, and can
        be toggled hidden without deleting its content.
      </p>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Panel List</h2>

      <div class="docs-screenshot">
        <img src="/assets/screenshots/admin-widget-panels-index.png" alt="Widget Panels list screenshot" />
      </div>

      <p class="docs-p">
        The panel list shows all available panels with their key and current visibility status.
        Click a panel's key link to open the editor. Use the <strong>Reload</strong> button to
        force the panel to refresh its cached output on the live site.
      </p>

      <div class="field-list">

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">header</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Content rendered at the top of every page, above the navigation. Typically used for
            the board's banner image, affiliate buttons, or announcement text.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">footer</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Content rendered at the bottom of every page. Typically used for affiliate links,
            credits, or supplementary navigation.
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Panel Editor</h2>

      <div class="docs-screenshot">
        <img src="/assets/screenshots/admin-widget-panels-edit.png" alt="Widget Panel editor screenshot" />
      </div>

      <p class="docs-p">
        The editor for each panel contains a rich text area and a visibility toggle.
      </p>

      <div class="field-list">

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Content</div>
            <div class="field-values">rich text / BBCode</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            The HTML or BBCode content displayed in this panel. The toolbar provides formatting
            shortcuts; you can also type BBCode directly.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Hidden</div>
            <div class="field-values">checkbox</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            When checked, the panel is not rendered on the live site. The content is preserved
            so you can re-enable the panel later without re-entering it.
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <p class="docs-p">
        Click <strong>Update</strong> to save changes. The panel is updated immediately.
      </p>
